doc.after: An example of a four dimensional second order antisymmetric tensor is the relativistic angular momentum which has six components three are the classical angular momentum and the other three are related to the boost of the center of mass of the system The derivative of the relativistic angular momentum with respect to proper time is the relativistic torque also second order antisymmetric tensor
